    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-10T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/1612: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-10T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >January 10, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 10—2:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Reference Department’s telegram No. 10, January 8, 7 p.m., strictly
                    confidential for myself only. I have seen the Ministers for <pb facs="0399"
                        n="389" xml:id="pg_389"/> Foreign Affairs and Finance and they both agree as
                    to the advisability of Prebisch remaining on in Washington for the reasons
                    stated by the Department. I understand that instructions to Prebisch in this
                    sense will be sent shortly.</p>
                <p>I stressed the need for absolute secrecy regarding any discussions that may take
                    place prior to action by Congress on aid to Britain legislation. They both
                    assured me that they understand the situation and would see that there would be
                    no leak here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
